      "raw_text": "WARDNER, Idaho. - Hereafter\nsaloons doing business here must\npay city license of $3.50 per year.\nThe council has decided the saloons\nmust help finance the city.\n\n\nLEWISTON, Idaho.-Harry New.\nman fell into the Clearwater river\nyesterday and was drowned. He\nwas 20 years old.\nGRANGEVILLE, Idaho. - Lee\nKing was chosen school superin-\ntendent at meeting last night. He\nIs graduate of the University Of\nMichigan.\n\n\nPULLMAN, Wash. - Whitman\nCounty Pomona grange, at meet\ning held here, arranged for the\nstate grange meeting, to be held\nhere June ITO."
